They note that both Republican- and Democratic-led states are among those that use widespread mail-in voting.
States with all mail-in elections automatically send ballots out to registered votes, while others require voters to request such a ballot.
Some states require mail-in ballots to be received by Election Day, while others only require that they be postmarked by then.
Citing the chaos in Wisconsin's primary, Texas Democrats filed a suit this week claiming that their state's restrictive mail-in voting rules are unconstitutional.